OL,3,CMen guilty of murdering man found
OL,4,C'chopped up' in suitcases
OL,6,FCocaine-fuelled McGlacken, 45,
OL,7,Fadmitted stabbing Mr Walsh, and then
OL,8,Fbrutally dismembering him before
OL,9,Fstuffing his remains in bin bags and
OL,10,Ftransferring them to a nearby park in
OL,11,Ffour suitcases.
OL,13,FMr Walsh was reported missing by his
OL,14,Ffamily.
OL,16,FManchester Crown Court heard his
OL,17,Fremains were only discovered after
OL,18,FEvitt broke down in custody and told
OL,19,Fpolice: "It's gone on too long. You're
OL,20,Fgoing to need a van. I need to show
OL,21,Fyou where he is."
