OL,3,CMen guilty of murdering man found
OL,4,C'chopped up' in suitcases
OL,6,FHe said the pair traded punches and
OL,7,Fclaimed that Mr Walsh hit him with a
OL,8,Fhammer.
OL,10,FEvitt said he had punched Mr Walsh,
OL,11,Fand then armed himself with the hammer
OL,12,Fand hit him over the head with it
OL,13,Fcausing him to collapse.
OL,15,FEvitt, who was 'very drunk', said he
OL,16,Fblacked out. He claimed that when he
OL,17,Fwoke up Mr Walsh was no longer there.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
