OL,3,CMen guilty of murdering man found
OL,4,C'chopped up' in suitcases
OL,6,FAt trial, McGlacken admitted
OL,7,F'decapitating and dismembering' Mr
OL,8,FWalsh. He also admitted stabbing him
OL,9,Fbut claimed he thought Mr Walsh was
OL,10,Falready dead when he knifed him.
OL,12,FAsked why he dismembered the body,
OL,13,FMcGlacken, who referred to Evitt as
OL,14,Fhis nephew, said: "To dispose of it. I
OL,15,Fneeded to get rid of it to protect my
OL,16,Fnephew."
OL,18,FHe explained the gruesome details of
OL,19,Fhow he'd 'chopped up' Mr Walsh's body
OL,20,Fusing a samurai sword, kitchen knives,
OL,21,Fa hammer and an electric saw.
